    "date": "2020-05-05T15:28:44Z",
    "text": "Clean Slate through Consolidation Act\n\nThis bill requires the Department of Education (ED) to have a record of default removed from a borrower's credit history in certain circumstances.\n\nSpecifically, when a borrower obtains a Federal Direct Consolidation Loan discharging the borrower's liability on a defaulted student loan, ED must request a consumer reporting agency remove the record of default from the borrower's credit history."
